innovation and experimentation

00:06:27.380 --> 00:06:31.690
in the arts since its founding
as the Heaton Gallery in 1950.

00:06:31.690 --> 00:06:33.710
And the Harvard Art
Museums together

00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:36.230
constitute one of the
leading research museums

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:40.100
worldwide These museums
represent very different kinds

00:06:40.100 --> 00:06:42.530
of institutions, but
each in their own way

00:06:42.530 --> 00:06:46.160
constitutes an important
part of the region's history

00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:49.460
and contributes vitally to
its character in the present.

00:06:49.460 --> 00:06:50.960
This evening, we're
fortunate enough

00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:53.030
to be able to engage
in conversation

00:06:53.030 --> 00:06:56.109
with their respective directors.

00:06:56.109 --> 00:06:57.650
They come from
different backgrounds,

00:06:57.650 --> 00:06:59.540
but all share a broad
set of experiences

00:06:59.540 --> 00:07:02.540
touching upon many different
aspects of the art world.

00:07:02.540 --> 00:07:05.960
They have curated exhibitions,
authored scholarly articles,

00:07:05.960 --> 00:07:08.090
purchased art,
hired museum staff,

00:07:08.090 --> 00:07:10.340
discovered new works,
written opinion pieces,

00:07:10.340 --> 00:07:13.250
founded NPOs, conceived
of innovative programs,

00:07:13.250 --> 00:07:15.730
crafted partnerships
and strategic plans

00:07:15.730 --> 00:07:19.370
in overseeing complex
building projects.

00:07:19.370 --> 00:07:22.820
They have also been
known to raise money.

00:07:22.820 --> 00:07:25.610
They are art lovers first
and foremost, but also

00:07:25.610 --> 00:07:30.320
scholars, historians, curators,
planners, educators, designers,

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:32.150
and leaders of the
community, as witnessed

00:07:32.150 --> 00:07:33.950
among other things in
the powerful letter

00:07:33.950 --> 00:07:36.800
cited by Dean Cohen that
they coauthored in February

00:07:36.800 --> 00:07:41.390
of this year to protest proposed
cuts to the National Endowment

00:07:41.390 --> 00:07:44.300
of the Arts and Humanities.

00:07:44.300 --> 00:07:46.310
In the summer of
2015, we were faced

00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:49.250
with an unusual circumstance
here in the Boston area.

00:07:49.250 --> 00:07:52.340
Three of the region's
museums, the Gardner, the MFA,

00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:54.380
and the Harvard Art
Museum, had vacancies

00:07:54.380 --> 00:07:56.300
in the director's position.

00:07:56.300 --> 00:07:59.570
There was a feeling that
once these seats were filled,

00:07:59.570 --> 00:08:00.980
there would
inevitably be a shift

00:08:00.980 --> 00:08:02.690
in the cultural landscape.

00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:05.180
We hoped to invite whoever
assumed these directorships

00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:07.400
to the Radcliffe Institute
in to participate

00:08:07.400 --> 00:08:10.490
in an event such as this one.

00:08:10.490 --> 00:08:13.580
However, time has a way of
passing, and at this point,

00:08:13.580 --> 00:08:17.180
they already seem like veterans
of our local art world.

00:08:17.180 --> 00:08:19.060
So we decided to
shoot for the moon

00:08:19.060 --> 00:08:21.890
