After a distinguished
and award winning career

00:11:02.460 --> 00:11:05.070
as a curator and author,
she became deputy director

00:11:05.070 --> 00:11:07.110
of art research
in Chicago, where

00:11:07.110 --> 00:11:09.450
she developed innovative
curatorial programming

00:11:09.450 --> 00:11:11.730
in partnerships with
local universities

00:11:11.730 --> 00:11:15.990
before coming to Harvard in 2016
as the Elizabeth ad John Moors

00:11:15.990 --> 00:11:19.390
Cabot Director of the
Harvard Art Museums.

00:11:19.390 --> 00:11:20.940
Matthew Teitelbaum
was previously

00:11:20.940 --> 00:11:25.950
a curator at the ICA Boston and
Mendel Art Gallery in Saskatoon

00:11:25.950 --> 00:11:28.110
before joining the
Art Gallery of Ontario

